    psychological: 'Nirvana is the psyche\'s vision of complete resolution — the state where all conflicts are dissolved, all needs are met, and the restless seeking that drives the ego finally comes to rest. The nirvana dream reflects a profound exhaustion with the game of desire and aversion, and a yearning for something that transcends both.',
    spiritual: 'Nirvana is not annihilation but the blowing out of the fires that obscure the mind\'s natural clarity and peace. The nirvana dream offers a glimpse of what consciousness looks like when it stops grasping — vast, clear, luminous, and fundamentally at peace. This glimpse can sustain practice through years of effort.',
    astrological: 'Nirvana connects to the 12th House of transcendence and Neptune\'s dissolution of all boundaries. The South Node\'s release of attachment and the North Node\'s evolutionary destination converge in nirvanic awareness. Pisces holds the oceanic quality of consciousness merged with its infinite source.',
    shadow: 'Nirvana pursued as escape from life rather than liberation within it warns of world-denial, spiritual bypassing, or the use of transcendence to avoid the messy work of being human. The shadow nirvana reveals where your desire for peace is actually a refusal to engage with suffering — yours or the world\'s.',
    reflection: 'Are you seeking peace — or are you seeking to disappear? And what is the difference?',
